article.description: — Keyshawn Feazell tied his career high with 22 points plus 11 rebounds as McNeese State narrowly defeated Southeastern Louisiana 95-91 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Feazell lifts McNeese St. past SE Louisiana 95-91
article.linkText: Feazell lifts McNeese St. past SE Louisiana 95-91
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- — Keyshawn Feazell tied his career high with 22 points plus 11 rebounds as McNeese State narrowly defeated Southeastern Louisiana 95-91 on Wednesday night. Carlos Rosario had 19 points and eight rebounds for McNeese State (9-11, 3-8 Southland Conference). Dru Kuxhausen added 14 points. Harwin Francois had 14 points. A.J. Lawson, the Cowboys’ second leading scorer entering the contest at 12 points per game, shot only 17% in the game (1 of 6). Southeastern Louisiana scored 57 second-half points, a season high for the team. Joe Kasperzyk scored a career-high 25 points for the Lions (7-14, 5-7). Nick Caldwell added 17 points and eight rebounds. Gus Okafor had 15 points. The Cowboys leveled the season series against the Lions. Southeastern Louisiana defeated McNeese State 92-88 on Jan. 20. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
